  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2022-06-16",
    "date": "2022-06-24T15:13:24Z",
    "text": "Community Development Investment Tax Credit Act of 2022\n\nThis bill allows a new tax credit for investment in Community Development Financial Institutions (CDFIs) to benefit underserved communities. The credit amount is a specified percentage of investment in a CDFI during successive ten year periods. The total credit amount is capped at $1 billion in 2022, $1.5 billion in 2023, and $2 billion in 2024 and each year thereafter, adjusted for inflation."
